Open the powershell(windows user) in the folder where you want to create the virtual environment
****************************************************************************************************
1. pip install --user virtualenv     (Install virtual env)

2. python -m virtualenv Martina      (Create a virtual environment called Martina)

3. .\Martina\Scripts\activate        (Activation the virtual environment)

4. deactivate                        (deactivate virtual environment)

5. To create the same environment in other systems we create the requirements.txt for the particular environment
pip freeze > requirements.txt (To create requirements.txt)

6. pip install -r .\requirements.txt  (To install all the versions in the requirements.txt)

7.python -m virtualenv --system-site-packages Martin (Creating a virtual environment with system Python requirement)

8.
>>>python
>>>import pandas
>>> pandas.__version__                 (To check a module version in Python)

Exercise: Create a virtual environment. In the virtual environment create a function to add two number.

